    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 min)</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pepperoni-and-kale-sauce-with-portobello-mushroom-tortelloni/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Boil a kettle and heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Slice your <strong>pepperoni</strong> into thin strips</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>pepperoni strips</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until starting to brown</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pepperoni-and-kale-sauce-with-portobello-mushroom-tortelloni/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and slice (don't chop!) your<strong> garlic</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>shredded kale</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pepperoni-and-kale-sauce-with-portobello-mushroom-tortelloni/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>portobello mushroom tortelloni</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the<strong> tortelloni </strong>for 3-4 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>tortelloni</strong>, reserving a cup of the<strong> starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pepperoni-and-kale-sauce-with-portobello-mushroom-tortelloni/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the pepperoni has started to brown, add the <strong>shredded kale </strong>and <strong>sliced garlic</strong> to the pan with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until the kale has wilted</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pepperoni-and-kale-sauce-with-portobello-mushroom-tortelloni/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once wilted, add your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong>, <strong>chopped tomatoes </strong>and <strong>dried oregano</strong> to the pan with a splash of <strong>starchy pasta water </strong>and cook for 1-2 min or until the sauce has slightly thickened</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pepperoni-and-kale-sauce-with-portobello-mushroom-tortelloni/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the sauce has thickened, add the <strong>drained tortelloni </strong>to the pan with a knob of <strong>butter </strong>and gently stir it all together until the pasta is coated in sauce \u2013 this is your<strong> pepperoni & kale sauce with portobello mushroom tortelloni</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash of starchy pasta water if your sauce is looking a little thick</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pepperoni-and-kale-sauce-with-portobello-mushroom-tortelloni/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>pepperoni & kale sauce with portobello mushroom tortelloni</strong> topped with your <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong></p><p>Season with a generous grind on <strong>black pepper</strong> and drizzle with a little <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
